ortant new essay-poem by Hall as well. It argues against irony from a rural perspective and amounts to Hall’s ars poetica. In an encompassing introduction, rob mclennan explores Hall’s four-plus decades of bricolage.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCanadian poetry. 4aLiterary Criticism: Canadian Literature. 4aPoetry. 7aPOETRY / Canadian.2bisacsh1 amclennan, rob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2015z978311127402708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2015z978311127703540uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978177112192740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781771121927423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781771121927/original  a978-3-11-127402-7  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-11-127703-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2015b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles